║                ULTIMATE BIOMETRIC DOOR LOCK                  ║
║                        WIRING DIAGRAM                        ║
║                        Arduino UNO                           ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

POWER (use breadboard rails)
├─ 5V rail  → All VCC connections
└─ GND rail → All GND connections (common ground!)

ARDUINO PIN → COMPONENT
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
5V           → Fingerprint Sensor VCC
             → LCD VCC
             → Relay VCC
             → Buzzer + (optional)
             
GND          → Fingerprint Sensor GND
             → LCD GND
             → Relay GND
             → Buzzer –
             → RGB LED cathode (long leg)
             → Push button (one leg)

A4           → LCD SDA
A5           → LCD SCL

2            → Fingerprint Sensor TX  (Software RX)
3            → Fingerprint Sensor RX  (Software TX)

5            → Active Buzzer (+)

6            → RGB LED Red     → 220Ω resistor
9            → RGB LED Green   → 220Ω resistor
10           → RGB LED Blue    → 220Ω resistor

8            → Push Button (other leg)

12           → Relay Module IN

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
LCD I2C Address: usually 0x27 (if blank screen → try 0x3F)

RGB LED: Common Cathode (long leg = GND)

Relay: 5V single-channel module (NO/COM for electric lock)

Push Button: Connected between Pin 8 and GND (internal pull-up used)
